SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: Cardiac arrest which occurs before a percutaneous coronary intervention can take place.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Cardiac Arrest Prior to Percutaneous Coronary Intervention

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: Access to the subject's vasculature is troublesome or formidable.
Placement of intracoronary devices across the coronary stenosis is troublesome or formidable.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: DIFFICULTY CROSSING THE CULPRIT LESION DURING THE PCI PROCEDURE
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Difficulty Crossing Culprit Lesion During Percutaneous Coronary Intervention

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: Endotracheal intubation which occurs before a percutaneous coronary intervention can take place.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Endotracheal Intubation before Percutaneous Coronary Intervention

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned. (NCI)
The subject has not provided consent in a timely manner for the procedure to take place.
